1
00:01:09,239 --> 00:01:09,840
Tang Yi

2
00:01:11,359 --> 00:01:12,239
I've been looking all over for you.

3
00:01:12,439 --> 00:01:13,239
So this is where you are.

4
00:01:14,079 --> 00:01:14,799
Heard Dr. Jiang here

5
00:01:14,879 --> 00:01:16,480
got a complaint on his first day.

6
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:17,760
So I came to show some love.

7
00:01:18,040 --> 00:01:19,760
He got a complaint? When?

8
00:01:21,239 --> 00:01:22,239
About ten minutes ago.

9
00:01:24,079 --> 00:01:25,439
Jiang Tiancai, you're really something.

10
00:01:25,599 --> 00:01:27,519
General Dentistry Department is always top.

11
00:01:27,640 --> 00:01:28,879
You show up and stain our record?

12
00:01:31,079 --> 00:01:31,719
Dr. Jiang.

13
00:01:32,159 --> 00:01:33,239
Take things as they come.

14
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:34,280
Look at me.

15
00:01:34,599 --> 00:01:35,680
I wanted to transfer over to help,

16
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:36,799
but I never got the chance.

17
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:39,959
Then stop getting in the way.

18
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:41,400
See yourself out.

19
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:45,799
Director Zeng sent me to inform you,

20
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:46,560
there's a meeting this afternoon.

21
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:47,480
Don't miss it.

22
00:01:50,439 --> 00:01:52,799
Then I'd better eat up and listen well.

23
00:01:53,359 --> 00:01:54,040
Senior.

24
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:55,680
Let's hit the cafeteria.

25
00:01:57,519 --> 00:01:59,760
Renowned cardiac surgeon Jiang Zhaohe

26
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,400
in heart valve replacement,

27
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:03,439
coronary bypass, and other complex surgeries,

28
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:04,959
has made remarkable contributions.

29
00:02:05,359 --> 00:02:07,959
At the Golden Scalpel Award ceremony,

30
00:02:08,159 --> 00:02:10,400
Professor Jiang gave us an exclusive interview.

31
00:02:21,879 --> 00:02:22,960
Family members, please step aside.

32
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:25,039
Tiancai.

33
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:26,159
Grandma.

34
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:27,000
Tiancai.

35
00:02:31,639 --> 00:02:32,560
Tiancai.

36
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:37,159
Doctor.

37
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:38,800
Have you seen my dad?

38
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:40,000
No, I haven't.

39
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:43,400
Doctor.

40
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:44,319
Have you seen my dad?

41
00:02:44,479 --> 00:02:45,120
Where is my dad?

42
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:46,039
Haven't seen him.

43
00:02:49,319 --> 00:02:49,800
Excuse me.

44
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,039
Have you seen where my dad is?

45
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:52,319
Haven't seen him.

46
00:02:52,439 --> 00:02:53,080
Why won't any of you tell me?

47
00:02:53,159 --> 00:02:53,800
Where is my dad?

48
00:02:53,919 --> 00:02:55,080
What are you all hiding from me?

49
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:56,280
Dr. Jiang is in the operating room.

50
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,439
A live Aortic Root Reconstruction surgery.

51
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:58,840
Every media outlet in the city is there.

52
00:02:59,039 --> 00:02:59,840
He can't step away.

53
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:19,719
Resuscitation efforts failed.

54
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:21,319
Time of clinical death,

55
00:03:21,639 --> 00:03:22,759
23:05.

56
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:52,520
The patient is a 74-year-old female.

57
00:03:52,719 --> 00:03:54,120
Due to a lower lip mass with erosion

58
00:03:54,439 --> 00:03:55,800
with a non-healing surface for two months,

59
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:57,520
she requested hospitalization for treatment.

60
00:03:58,080 --> 00:04:00,080
Examination revealed a right lower lip mass

61
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:02,280
approximately 2.5 centimeters in size,

62
00:04:02,639 --> 00:04:04,840
with surface erosion and a firm base.

63
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:07,439
We took a sample of the patient's

64
00:04:07,599 --> 00:04:08,639
local lesion tissue for a biopsy.

65
00:04:08,879 --> 00:04:09,800
The pathology report confirmed

66
00:04:10,039 --> 00:04:12,560
an early-stage right lower lip

67
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,439
Well-differentiated Squamous Cell Carcinoma.

68
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:17,160
The patient is elderly,

69
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,800
with longstanding CHD and on medication.

70
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,199
Her cardiac function is still acceptable.

71
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:22,879
The patient is also an educated woman

72
00:04:23,279 --> 00:04:24,279
who has high expectations

73
00:04:24,879 --> 00:04:27,120
for her quality of life and appearance.

74
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:28,759
She is eager for treatment.

75
00:04:29,279 --> 00:04:30,480
So she hopes our hospital

76
00:04:30,879 --> 00:04:32,160
can provide the optimal treatment plan

77
00:04:32,519 --> 00:04:33,720
as soon as possible.

78
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:36,000
That's pretty much the situation.

79
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:37,639
If anyone has any questions,

80
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:38,759
feel free to speak up.

81
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,800
Don't hold back, alright?

82
00:04:41,879 --> 00:04:43,600
The good thing about her tumor

83
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:46,000
is it's early-stage and well-differentiated.

84
00:04:46,279 --> 00:04:47,720
The prognosis is relatively good.

85
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:50,720
But given her age and CHD history,

86
00:04:51,319 --> 00:04:53,319
the surgical risk is still relatively high.

87
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:54,399
I think

88
00:04:54,519 --> 00:04:56,399
we could try some localized radiation therapy

89
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:57,519
and see how it works.

90
00:04:57,839 --> 00:05:00,160
But radiation's local control rate

91
00:05:00,319 --> 00:05:01,279
isn't as good as surgery.

92
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:03,839
Based on her cardiac function assessment,

93
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:06,879
we can simply excise the lesion directly.

94
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,720
The defect can then

95
00:05:08,959 --> 00:05:09,959
be closed with direct suturing.

96
00:05:10,399 --> 00:05:12,199
The post-op lower lip shape may be off,

97
00:05:12,399 --> 00:05:13,759
but the procedure is relatively simple

98
00:05:14,079 --> 00:05:14,920
and safer.

99
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:17,160
But that way,

100
00:05:17,399 --> 00:05:19,600
the resulting microstomia deformity

101
00:05:20,439 --> 00:05:22,560
may be hard for the patient to accept.

102
00:05:22,759 --> 00:05:24,120
She's already 74.

103
00:05:24,319 --> 00:05:26,040
A minor deformity won't affect her much.

104
00:05:26,639 --> 00:05:27,720
Besides, after a year,

105
00:05:27,959 --> 00:05:29,240
if the tumor doesn't recur,

106
00:05:29,519 --> 00:05:31,040
we can do secondary reconstructive surgery.

107
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:32,959
Whether her physical condition

108
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,480
can withstand a second surgery

109
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:35,439
is uncertain.

110
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,680
Since we can repair it in one go

111
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,480
and give her a better quality of life,

112
00:05:39,879 --> 00:05:41,079
why settle for second best?

113
00:05:41,519 --> 00:05:42,439
A one-time repair?

114
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:43,879
How confident are you?

115
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:46,839
Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery prioritizes

116
00:05:47,319 --> 00:05:48,519
function first. Only after ensuring that

117
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:49,480
do we consider aesthetics.

118
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,920
I get young people wanting to prove themselves,

119
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:54,199
but don't gamble with a patient's life.

120
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:03,240
We need to be more rigorous.

121
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:05,079
Alright, alright, stop arguing, everyone.

122
00:06:05,319 --> 00:06:07,079
Let's hear Director Zeng's opinion first.

123
00:06:07,959 --> 00:06:09,040
I think for this case,

124
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,319
after excising the lower lip lesion,

125
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:12,800
we can simultaneously repair it with an

126
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:15,279
ipsilateral Buccal Mucosal Flip Advancement Flap.

127
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:17,199
The post-repair appearance is aesthetic,

128
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:19,079
and mouth opening is largely unaffected.

129
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:27,720
Old Zhang,

130
00:06:27,959 --> 00:06:28,639
see that?

131
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,839
The new generation surpasses the old.

132
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,560
Hey, Jiang Tiancai,

133
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,079
don't keep hiding in the back.

134
00:06:34,639 --> 00:06:36,160
Come up front and explain it to everyone.

135
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:37,639
Let's all hear it, alright?

136
00:06:37,879 --> 00:06:38,519
Give him a hand.

137
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:58,720
Dr. Chen.

138
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,519
We can see

139
00:07:03,079 --> 00:07:05,399
since this patient's case is quite unique,

140
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:06,480
Don't go through their notes.

141
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:07,399
Mind your own business.

142
00:07:07,639 --> 00:07:08,600
we should design

143
00:07:08,839 --> 00:07:10,319
a targeted treatment plan.

144
00:07:11,639 --> 00:07:12,680
In the early stages of treatment,

145
00:07:12,959 --> 00:07:14,879
communicate effectively with the family.

146
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:17,040
So rude and pretentious.

147
00:07:17,639 --> 00:07:19,319
Isn't this the same as what Dr. Chen wrote?

148
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:21,120
Dr. Chen didn't even say anything,

149
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:23,040
yet he rushes to show off.

150
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:24,480
Look at this.

151
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:25,439
Dr. Jiang, take a look for me.

152
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:28,360
Here, and here too.

153
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:29,319
This part, right?

154
00:07:29,839 --> 00:07:31,160
Thank you so much. I'll revise it right away.

155
00:07:35,759 --> 00:07:37,199
Does this section need revising too?

156
00:07:37,879 --> 00:07:39,319
Your treatment approach here is fine.

157
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:41,759
Thank you, thank you.

158
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:46,360
Dr. Tang.

159
00:07:46,839 --> 00:07:48,959
Seems General Dentistry Department is slipping.

160
00:07:49,399 --> 00:07:50,439
Doing Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery now?

161
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:52,240
Are you two here to give us pointers now?

162
00:07:53,079 --> 00:07:54,160
Pointers? I wouldn't dare.

163
00:07:54,439 --> 00:07:56,160
Me? You're never too old to learn.

164
00:07:56,319 --> 00:07:56,920
True enough.

165
00:07:57,319 --> 00:07:58,399
The work in your department,

166
00:07:58,560 --> 00:07:59,680
pulling teeth, filling cavities,

167
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:00,959
isn't very challenging.

168
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:03,240
How about transferring to our department?

169
00:08:03,519 --> 00:08:05,240
I'll teach you what real skill looks like.

170
00:08:10,199 --> 00:08:11,879
I dare you to never get a toothache.

171
00:08:26,319 --> 00:08:27,680
Basal infiltration at twelve o'clock.

172
00:08:27,879 --> 00:08:28,959
Recommend expanding excision by 2mm.

173
00:08:30,279 --> 00:08:31,279
Mind the nerves.

174
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:32,480
Give me more visibility.

175
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:39,679
Have you ever seen a surgery this complex?

176
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:44,840
Clean and precise.

177
00:08:46,759 --> 00:08:47,679
There's quite a bit of bleeding.

178
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:48,960
Stop the bleeding first.

179
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:49,759
Hemostat.

180
00:08:51,159 --> 00:08:51,720
Blood pressure?

181
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:53,840
150 over 90.

182
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:55,960
Quick hands.

183
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:56,840
Ligate.

184
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:58,159
Retrograde margin.

185
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:00,279
Reverse dissection along the oral commissure.

186
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:22,320
Send for frozen section.

187
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:26,320
The specimen removal went reasonably well.

188
00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:29,399
Now it depends on the flap transfer.

189
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:32,120
This is the main event today.

190
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:36,879
Impressive, right?

191
00:09:37,879 --> 00:09:38,840
The values look fine.

192
00:09:44,759 --> 00:09:46,360
Director Zeng, Negative margin.

193
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:50,360
Now beginning buccal mucosal flap preparation.

194
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:52,159
Preserve the buccal branch of the facial artery.

195
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:02,480
Gauze.

196
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:05,639
Stop the bleeding.

197
00:10:05,799 --> 00:10:06,720
I can't even see the bleeding point.

198
00:10:07,639 --> 00:10:09,120
Find the bleeding artery! Start a transfusion!

199
00:10:16,759 --> 00:10:17,320
Blood pressure?

200
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:18,559
160 over 56.

201
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:19,360
Heart rate?

202
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:20,240
95.

203
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:21,200
Blood loss?

204
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:22,320
150.
